# Plan Entitlement and Free Trial Frontend Brief

## Status
proposed

## Problem
Frontend must align with updated backend entitlement and free-trial contracts without assuming any missing plan-management APIs. Access control and user messaging must be driven by contract-defined auth payloads and entitlement error responses.

## Scope
- Contract-aligned UX for login, email verification, subject/question access, and practice generation entitlement blocks.
- Surface free/pro plan behavior using existing API responses only.
- Handle entitlement-specific `403` responses from practice generation with distinct UI messages.
- Route free users to `/pricing` when they attempt pro-only features.

## Out of Scope
- Any new billing, checkout, payment status, or subscription lifecycle endpoints.
- Any backend contract changes.
- Any feature depending on non-existent plan/trial API routes (contract gap).
- In-app subscription mutation to pro (no contract endpoint exists for this yet).

## Screens and Routes
- `/login`
  - Submit credentials.
  - Handle unverified-account flow (`401` with `Email verification required`) and resend verification CTA.
- `/signup`
  - Register and show "check your email" success state.
  - Link to verification help/resend flow.
- `/verify-email?token=<token>` (new frontend route required by contract note)
  - Read `token` query param and verify email.
- `/subjects`
  - Auth-required subject list; unauthorized redirects or auth error state.
- `/subjects/[slug]`
  - Auth-required question discovery and practice setup entry.
- `/practice/[id]`
  - Practice session route entered only after successful generation.
- `/pricing`
  - Destination route for upgrade CTA when entitlement blocks occur.
  - Shows request-upgrade path only; cannot finalize upgrade in-app without backend endpoint.

## UX States
- `/login`
  - `loading`: disable submit and show pending state.
  - `error`: invalid credentials (`400/401`), unverified email (`401` specific message).
  - `success`: store token/user and navigate to authenticated area.
  - `empty`: initial untouched form.
- `/signup`
  - `loading`: disable submit during register call.
  - `error`: validation or conflict (`400/409`) and unexpected failure (`500`).
  - `success`: confirmation that verification email was sent.
  - `empty`: initial form.
- `/verify-email`
  - `loading`: verifying token.
  - `error`: invalid/expired/used/already-verified (`400`) and rate-limit (`429`).
  - `success`: show brief success confirmation, then auto-redirect to `/login`.
  - `empty`: missing `token` query param (client-side invalid state).
- `/subjects`
  - `loading`: skeleton/list loader.
  - `error`: unauthorized (`401`) or server error.
  - `success`: subject list rendered.
  - `empty`: no subjects for selected exam type.
- `/subjects/[slug]` (question/practice setup)
  - `loading`: fetch questions/setup data.
  - `error`: unauthorized (`401`), bad filter (`400`), not found (`404`).
  - `success`: valid setup form and generate action.
  - `empty`: no questions in selected filter scope.
- Practice generation action (from `/subjects/[slug]`)
  - `loading`: disable generate button and show progress.
  - `error`: `400/401/404` plus entitlement `403` mapped to message-specific UI and upgrade CTA.
  - `pro-gated`: free users attempting CQ/MIXED are sent to `/pricing`.
  - `success`: navigate to `/practice/{practice_session_id}`; show partial-generation warning when returned.
  - `empty`: no setup selected yet.

## Exact Endpoints Used (from `project_docs/CONTRACTS/api.md`)
- `POST /api/auth/register` (signup)
- `POST /api/auth/login` (login)
- `GET /api/auth/me` (hydrate auth + `plan_tier`)
- `POST /api/auth/verify-email` (verify route)
- `POST /api/auth/resend-verification` (unverified flow)
- `GET /api/subjects` (authenticated subjects listing)
- `GET /api/questions` (authenticated question discovery)
- `POST /api/practice/generate` (entitlement-aware session generation)

No additional plan/trial endpoint exists in current contracts; frontend must not call any invented `/plan`, `/trial`, or billing APIs.
No dedicated endpoint exists to upgrade a subscription to pro from frontend in this phase.

## Validation Rules (mirror schemas)
- `POST /api/auth/register`
  - Follow `project_docs/CONTRACTS/schemas/auth.register.post.json` exactly (body shape, required fields, no extra properties).
- `POST /api/auth/login` (`schemas/auth.login.post.json`)
  - Body required: `email:string`, `password:string`.
  - No extra body/query properties.
- `GET /api/auth/me` (`schemas/auth.me.get.json`)
  - No query/body fields.
  - Response user includes `plan_tier` enum: `free | pro`.
- `POST /api/auth/verify-email` (`schemas/auth.verify-email.post.json`)
  - Body required: `token:string`.
  - No additional properties.
- `POST /api/auth/resend-verification` (`schemas/auth.resend-verification.post.json`)
  - Body required: `email:string`.
  - No additional properties.
- `GET /api/subjects` (`schemas/subjects.get.json`)
  - Query optional: `exam_type:string` (defaults handled server-side).
  - No additional query/body properties.
- `GET /api/questions` (`schemas/questions.list.get.json`)
  - Query required: `exam_type_id:integer`, `subject_id:integer`.
  - Query optional: `chapter_id:integer`, `question_type:string`, `language:string`.
  - No additional query/body properties.
- `POST /api/practice/generate` (`schemas/practice.generate.post.json`)
  - Body required: `exam_type_id:integer`, `subject_id:integer`, `mode:string`, `selection:object`.
  - `mode`: backend allows `MCQ|CQ|MIXED` (case-normalized server-side).
  - `selection.type`: backend allows `CHAPTERS|FULL_SYLLABUS` (case-normalized server-side).
  - `selection.chapter_ids`: integer array, `minItems: 1` when provided.
  - Optional numeric fields accepted by contract: `mcq_count`, `mcqCount`, `mcq_requested`, `cq_count`, `cqCount`, `cq_requested`.
  - No additional body/query properties.

## Tests To Add
- Contract-mapper unit tests
  - Map `POST /api/practice/generate` `403` messages by exact backend message string to correct entitlement UI states and upgrade CTA behavior.
  - Ensure non-entitlement errors (`400/401/404/500`) use generic error handling.
- Auth flow tests
  - Login handles unverified `401` with resend-verification path.
  - Verify-email page handles `200`, `400`, and `429`.
  - Resend-verification handles `200`, `400`, `429`, `500`.
- Data access guard tests
  - `/api/subjects` and `/api/questions` unauthorized (`401`) flow in UI.
- Request validation tests (frontend payload builder)
  - Reject missing required fields per schema before request.
  - Reject additional properties not allowed by schema contracts.
  - Enforce required query params for `/api/questions`.
- Integration tests (route level)
  - `/subjects` and `/subjects/[slug]` loading/empty/error/success states.
  - Practice generation success navigates to `/practice/[id]`.
  - Practice generation `warning` payload is surfaced to user.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Frontend only uses endpoints listed above and none outside current contracts.
- All listed routes implement loading/empty/error/success states.
- Payload/query shapes match schema constraints.
- Entitlement-specific `403` responses from practice generation produce distinct UX outcomes.
- Free-user attempts to access pro-only features always expose a `/pricing` path.
- Test coverage includes auth, entitlement, and guarded data-access paths.

## Risks
- Contract provides entitlement outcomes by message text, not stable machine-readable error codes; UI mapping may be brittle if backend wording changes.
- No dedicated plan/trial endpoint means plan state visibility is limited to `plan_tier` and request-time entitlement failures.

